wikipedia_page.main: Dr Irene Daw (13 February 1941 – 30 October 2010) was a British sports shooter and Olympian. Daw represented Great Britain at the 1984 Summer Olympics, the first Olympic Games to include 10 meter Air Rifle. At the 1979 ISSF World Shooting Championships, she won a Bronze medal as part of the Women's Air Rifle Team.
